Mexico
[1] Jalisco: bat, human death
Date: Wed 27 Apr 2022
Source: Outbreak News Today [edited]
http://outbreaknewstoday.com/mexico-first-human-rabies-case-in-jalisco-in-years-79246/


Mexico: 1st human rabies case in Jalisco in years
-------------------------------------------------
A 41-year-old man from El Salto, Jalisco died from rabies on [18 Apr 2022], the 1st such case reported in the state in years.

On 14 Apr 2022, the Mexican Institute of Social Security (IMSS) notified a case of rabies in a human in the state: a patient who in January [2022] suffered a bat bite on his right hand, which occurred in the municipality of Chapala.

He did not consult with a doctor until 9 Apr 2022 when he began feeling pain in the arm where he was bit.

On [13 Apr 2022], he was taken to the IMSS National Western Medical Center emergency room, where he was isolated and an anti-rabies vaccination scheme was started. Without presenting improvement, the patient died on [18 Apr 2022].

A sample was processed at the State Public Health Laboratory of Jalisco (LESP) and showed a positive result for rabies.

The health authorities of the state of Jalisco immediately proceeded to carry out surveillance and identification of risk contacts, as well as preventive treatment patient contacts.

In Jalisco, the last case of human rabies due to a dog bite occurred in 1995. From 1996 to 2021 there have been only 7 cases associated with wild animal species, the last case was in 2009 in a bovine.

