Communicated by:
ProMED

[Bites from bats can be quite bad. Bats can bite a sleeping individual without waking the person. If a bat should land, drop, or perch on you in any fashion, please seek medical care immediately. They can bite without you knowing it. There is a limited amount of time from bite to initiation of post exposure prophylaxis [PEP]. If too much time has passed since the exposure, the PEP may not be effective.

If you are bitten or scratched by any animal, please seek immediate medical attention, especially if the animal is wild or you have no history of the animal having been vaccinated.

Please vaccinate your livestock. Horses, cattle, sheep and goats can be exposed to rabies. Most frequently it occurs from a skunk. These furry little creatures wander through the pasture with an odd way of moving which attracts the attention of the nearby stock. The animal often puts its nose down to the creature and gets its nose bitten and thus the rabies virus moves to a new victim.

Rabies virus is deadly to animals. Rabid animals can inflict damage to the human body, such as a horse or cow charging or trampling a human, or a dog biting. Please vaccinate your animals, for your safety, for their safety. - Mod.TG

